      "content": "Originalism is grounded in the legal principle that the Constitution is a binding contract among the people, not a living document subject to the whims of judges. Proponents argue that only the text ratified by the Founding generation should limit government power, ensuring that the Framers' intent remains the supreme law rather than being rewritten by unelected officials. This approach provides stability and predictability for the legal system, preventing the judiciary from overstepping its authority to enact policy preferences. Ultimately, originalism is the only method that respects the democratic legitimacy of the Constitution as a fixed framework for governance.",
