      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but some people argue that because the original meaning of the text can be so hard to pin down, judges end up just picking whatever historical fact supports their own view anyway. isn't it kind of a stretch to say it's a \"neutral\" way to find the law if the history is always debatable?",
